The political landscape was further complicated by a series of party mergers, splits and short‑lived coalitions that had emerged in the aftermath of the 1993 election. The [Japan Socialist Party](/Social_Democratic_Party_(Japan)) (JSP), which had previously governed in coalition with the LDP, fractured under the pressures of the new electoral system, ultimately giving rise to the [Democratic Party](/Democratic_Party_(Japan,_1996)) (DP) as a third‑force alternative.

